5|$|After {{maintaining}} an informal public distance for eight years, Bill Clinton and Gore reunited {{for the media}} in August 2009 after Clinton arranged {{for the release of}} two journalists who were being held <b>hostage</b> <b>in</b> North Korea. The two women were employees of Gore's Current TV.|$|E
5|$|Pyrrhus {{attempted}} to goad Antigonus into fighting a pitched battle {{on the plain}} in front of Argos but the Macedonian king was unmoved. The Argives sent ambassadors to both kings, beseeching them to respect the city's neutrality. Antigonus agreed to the Argives' terms and gave his son as a <b>hostage</b> <b>in</b> order to demonstrate his sincerity. While Pyrrhus agreed to retreat from Argos, he failed to give a pledge {{and as a result}} was regarded with suspicion.|$|E
